HEADWORD: Firmer-chisel
<hw>Firm"er-chis"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A chisel, thin
in proportion to its width. It has a tang to enter the handle instead of
a socket for receiving it.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Firmitude</ent>⟦br⟧
